<h2>Today I am goning to learin about attributes and tags</h2><br>
<p>From what I have learned an attribute specifies the tag.<br>
A tag is how you define a certain handeling, you always start your attribute with a start.<br>
An attribute gives additional info about the elemant.<br>
Attributes are usually made by typing name="value".<br>
alt - text or image <br>
href - URL for a link <br>
id - specifies a unique id for an element <br>
src - specifies the URL for an image <br>
style - specifies a inline CSS style. <br></p>


